# Git Workflow Rules

## Pre-Commit Requirements

**Before every commit:**
1. Run `npm run build` - fix all errors
2. Run `npm run lint` - fix all warnings
3. Ensure package.json and package-lock.json are in sync

Pre-commit hooks automatically verify these (install with `npm run hooks:install`).

## Package Management

### Always Keep Files in Sync

```bash
# Adding packages
npm install <package>        # Updates both files

# Removing packages
npm uninstall <package>      # Updates both files

# After package.json changes
npm install                  # Regenerates lock file
```

### Red Flags

❌ Committing only package.json without package-lock.json
❌ Committing only package-lock.json without package.json
❌ Manually editing package-lock.json

### Fix Sync Issues

```bash
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm install
```

## Database Files (Template Exception)

**This is a TEMPLATE repository** - database files ARE committed:

```bash
# These commands are CORRECT for this template:
git add db/prod.db
git add -A  # Includes .db files
```

- `db/prod.db` provides working sample data
- Do NOT add `*.db` to `.gitignore`
- Do NOT warn about database commits in this repo

## Commit Message Format

```
Brief description of change

- Specific change 1
- Specific change 2

🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
```

## Build Verification

The build must pass before committing:

```bash
npm run build
```

Fix these before committing:
- TypeScript errors
- Missing dependencies
- Import/export issues
- Configuration errors

## Quick Checklist

- [ ] `npm run build` passes
- [ ] `npm run lint` passes
- [ ] package.json and package-lock.json both staged (if either changed)
- [ ] Meaningful commit message
- [ ] No secrets in committed files
